  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They had some Red Cross [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] files that apparently [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] carried her as, as, for, for dead.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] These files may have been also compiled by people who came, who returned, who would tell them that so-and-so did not survive.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The next step, again, was to be sent somewhere for delousing or for, for fumigation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we were-- a couple of us were sent to a rehabilitation [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] place, which was in the countryside.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And was a-- there were string of castles that were before the war owned by [INAUDIBLE], who owned a, a lot of the industry in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] These castles were expropriated because they were of German origin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it was the first time that we slept on a regular bed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I even had a nightgown, was embroidered name of count.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we set the tables and used forks and knives, which was something that we haven't done for three years.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, these were all children, mostly orphans, who, who were just there in the country and played in gardens and, and ate food.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were volunteers, I guess, who took care of us and tried to bring us back home alive.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We started writing our memoirs there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The drawing that I showed you, I actually drew for several of the boys.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And years later, they showed it to me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were together, starting our memoirs because we-- at that time, we wanted to somehow record what we still remembered.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's amazing what memory does.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because when I read what I wrote that year in 1945, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sometimes is reading the story of somebody else.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
